"title": "5447: poverty, causes of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5447",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>To want for the necessities of life is ultimately the result of human sin.</p>\n<h2>Poverty arises from human sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a></strong> <em>Compare this with the description of Eden in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:9-Gen2:14\">Ge 2:9–14</a>.</em></p>\n<h2>Causes of poverty</h2>\n<h3>Divine retribution brings poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:47-Deut28:48\">DEU 28:47–28:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:16\">PRO 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:1\">ISA 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:6\">AMO 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11\">AMO 5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Idleness brings poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:10-Prov6:11\">PRO 6:10–6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:4\">PRO 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:23\">PRO 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:13\">PRO 20:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:33-Prov24:34\">PRO 24:33–24:34</a></p>\n<h3>Dissolute living brings poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:17\">PRO 21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:26\">PRO 6:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:19\">PRO 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:14\">LUK 15:14</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of discipline brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:18\">PRO 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:5\">PRO 21:5</a></p>\n<h3>Rash promises bring poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:26-Prov22:27\">PRO 22:26–22:27</a></p>\n<h3>Debt brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:23-Matt18:25\">MAT 18:23–18:25</a></p>\n<h3>Neglect of God's law of giving brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:24\">PRO 11:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:22\">PRO 28:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a></p>\n<h3>Neglect of God's work brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:9\">HAG 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Oppression brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:6\">JDG 6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:19\">JOB 20:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:23\">PRO 13:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:7\">ISA 1:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Famine brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:11\">GEN 45:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:20-Gen47:21\">GEN 47:20–47:21</a></p>\n<h3>Misfortune brings poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:13-Job1:21\">JOB 1:13–1:21</a> <em>These trials were inflicted by Satan but allowed by God as a test of Job's faith.</em></p>\n<h2>Poverty affects good as well as evil people</h2>\n<h3>The righteous often escape poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:9\">DEU 8:7–8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:9-Ps34:10\">PSA 34:9–34:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25\">PSA 37:25</a></p>\n<h3>Many of the godly have been poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:20\">LUK 16:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:26\">ROM 15:26</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:20\">MAT 8:20</a></p>\n<h2>Results of poverty</h2>\n<h3>Poverty results in ruin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:15\">PRO 10:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Poverty results in shame</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:18\">PRO 13:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:3\">LUK 16:3</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty results in misery</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:7\">PRO 31:7</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty results in crime</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:30\">PRO 6:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:8-Prov30:9\">PRO 30:8–30:9</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty need not lead to ungodliness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:71\">PSA 119:71</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:44\">MRK 12:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:4\">LUK 21:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:2\">2CO 8:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5\">JAS 2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:9\">REV 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Voluntary poverty</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's example of voluntary poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Voluntary poverty commanded of some</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21-Matt19:22\">MAT 19:21–19:22</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ did not say this to everyone.</em></p>\n<h3>Voluntary poverty experienced by others</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:34\">HEB 10:34</a></p>\n<h3>Love essential in voluntary poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:3\">1CO 13:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:10\">2CO 6:10</a></p>",
